# 🔵 When Should You Split Components?

Think like this:

> One component = One responsibility

If a component is doing too many things → split it.

---

# 🧠 Rule 1: If It Gets Too Big

If your component:

* Has 200+ lines
* Too much JSX
* Hard to read

👉 Split it.

---

### ❌ Bad Example (Everything in One File)

```jsx
function Dashboard() {
  return (
    <div>
      <Header />
      <UserProfile />
      <ProductList />
      <Footer />
    </div>
  );
}
```

If you write all this inside one big file → messy.

---

### ✅ Better Way

Split into:

* Header.js
* UserProfile.js
* ProductList.js
* Footer.js

Clean. Reusable. Easy to maintain.

---

# 🧠 Rule 2: If UI Part Can Be Reused

If you see repetition → split it.

---

### ❌ Repeating Code

```jsx
<li>Java</li>
<li>Spring</li>
<li>React</li>
```

Better:

```jsx
function Skill({ name }) {
  return <li>{name}</li>;
}
```

Now reusable everywhere.

---

# 🧠 Rule 3: If It Has Its Own Logic

If a part:

* Has its own state
* Has its own event handlers
* Has its own conditional rendering

👉 It should be its own component.

---

### Example

Instead of:

```jsx
function App() {
  const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);

  // 200 lines of modal code here...
}
```

Better:

```jsx
function Modal({ isOpen }) {
  if (!isOpen) return null;
  return <div>Modal Content</div>;
}
```

---

# 🧠 Rule 4: Separation of Concerns

Ask:

👉 Is this UI logically a separate piece?

Example:

* Navigation bar
* Sidebar
* Card
* Button
* Modal
* Form

All should be separate components.

---

# 🔵 Real Project Thinking

Big App
⬇
Pages
⬇
Sections
⬇
Small UI Components

Like:

```
App
 ├── Dashboard
 │     ├── StatsCard
 │     ├── Chart
 │     └── ActivityList
 └── Settings
       ├── ProfileForm
       └── PasswordForm
```

---

# 🧠 When NOT to Split

Don’t split if:

❌ Component is very small
❌ Used only once and very simple
❌ Splitting makes it more complicated

Over-splitting is also bad.

---

# 🔥 Golden Rule (Very Important)

If you cannot explain what the component does in one sentence →
It is probably doing too much.

